ChangeLog for rust-ed

2025-11-05  Brian Boynton, MD  <brian@example.org>

	* GNU Standards Compliance: Complete licensing and documentation

	* COPYING: Added GNU GPL v3 license text
	* NEWS: Created user-visible changes file for version 0.1.0
	* AUTHORS: Created primary author listing
	* THANKS: Created contributors acknowledgment file
	* INSTALL: Created detailed installation instructions

	* doc/rust-ed.texi: Created Texinfo manual based on GNU ed structure
	* doc/fdl.texi: Copied GNU Free Documentation License

	* Cargo.toml (license): Changed from "MIT OR Apache-2.0" to "GPL-3.0-or-later"

	* src/*.rs: Added GPL v3 copyright headers to all source files:
	  - src/main.rs: Main entry point
	  - src/buffer.rs: Line buffer management
	  - src/main_loop.rs: Command execution loop
	  - src/error.rs: Error handling
	  - src/io.rs: File I/O operations
	  - src/global.rs: Global command implementation
	  - src/regex.rs: Regular expression interface
	  - src/signal.rs: Signal handling
	  - src/carg_parser.rs: Argument parser

	* docs/GNU-STANDARDS-COMPLIANCE.md: Created compliance tracking document

2025-10-29  Brian Boynton, MD  <brian@example.org>

	* Project Restructuring: Implemented modular differential testing

	* tests/differential_containerized.rs: Main test runner with 119 tests
	* tests/common/suites/: Created 27 test suite files (one per command)
	  - cmd_append.rs, cmd_change.rs, cmd_delete.rs, cmd_insert.rs
	  - cmd_print.rs, cmd_quit.rs, cmd_edit.rs, cmd_filename.rs
	  - cmd_read.rs, cmd_write.rs, cmd_list.rs, cmd_number.rs
	  - cmd_equals.rs, cmd_move.rs, cmd_copy.rs, cmd_join.rs
	  - cmd_substitute.rs, cmd_global.rs, cmd_undo.rs, cmd_mark.rs
	  - cmd_yank.rs, cmd_put.rs, cmd_scroll.rs, cmd_shell.rs
	  - cmd_comment.rs, cmd_newline.rs, cmd_help.rs

	* tests/README.md: Documented test structure and organization
	* docs/modular-differential-testing-framework.md: Framework guide

2025-10-28  Brian Boynton, MD  <brian@example.org>

	* Docker Testing Infrastructure: Set up containerized testing

	* docker/Dockerfile.gnu-ed: GNU ed 1.22.2 reference container
	* docker/Dockerfile.rust-ed: rust-ed test container
	* docker/Dockerfile.test-runner: Automated test runner

	* gnu-ed-source/ed-1.22.2/: Added GNU ed source for reference
	* gnu-ed-source/VERSION.txt: Documented target version

2025-10-15  Brian Boynton, MD  <brian@example.org>

	* Core Implementation: All 32 GNU ed commands

	* src/main_loop.rs (main_loop): Main command execution loop
	* src/main_loop.rs (execute_*_command): All 32 command implementations
	  - execute_append_command: 'a' command
	  - execute_change_command: 'c' command
	  - execute_delete_command: 'd' command
	  - execute_insert_command: 'i' command
	  - execute_print_command: 'p' command
	  - execute_list_command: 'l' command
	  - execute_number_command: 'n' command
	  - execute_equals_command: '=' command
	  - execute_edit_command: 'e' and 'E' commands
	  - execute_filename_command: 'f' command
	  - execute_read_command: 'r' command
	  - execute_write_command: 'w', 'W', 'wq' commands
	  - execute_quit_command: 'q' and 'Q' commands
	  - execute_substitute_command: 's' command with all flags
	  - execute_global_command: 'g' and 'v' commands
	  - execute_interactive_global_command: 'G' and 'V' commands
	  - execute_move_command: 'm' command
	  - execute_copy_command: 't' command
	  - execute_join_command: 'j' command
	  - execute_undo_command: 'u' command
	  - execute_mark_command: 'k' command
	  - execute_yank_command: 'y' command
	  - execute_put_command: 'x' command
	  - execute_scroll_command: 'z' command
	  - execute_shell_command: '!' command
	  - execute_help_command: 'h' and 'H' commands
	  - execute_prompt_command: 'P' command
	  - execute_comment_command: '#' command
	  - execute_newline_command: newline command

	* src/buffer.rs (EdBuffer): Line buffer with undo support
	* src/buffer.rs (push_undo_state): Undo stack management
	* src/buffer.rs (clear_undo_stack): Undo stack clearing (GNU ed behavior)

	* src/io.rs (read_file): File reading with proper newline handling
	* src/io.rs (write_file): File writing with atomic operations
	* src/io.rs (read_shell_output): Shell command execution
	* src/io.rs (write_to_shell): Pipe to shell commands

	* src/regex.rs (compile_regex): Regular expression compilation
	* src/regex.rs (find_matching_line): Pattern matching with wrapping
	* src/regex.rs (is_case_insensitive_match): Case-insensitive support

	* src/global.rs (execute_global): Global command implementation
	* src/global.rs (mark_matching_lines): Two-pass global algorithm

	* src/signal.rs (setup_signal_handlers): POSIX signal handling
	* src/signal.rs (handle_sigint): Interrupt handling
	* src/signal.rs (handle_sighup): Hangup handling with ed.hup recovery

2025-10-01  Brian Boynton, MD  <brian@example.org>

	* Initial Project Setup

	* Cargo.toml: Created project with dependencies
	  - clap 4.4: Command-line argument parsing
	  - regex 1.10: POSIX-compatible regular expressions
	  - thiserror 1.0: Error handling
	  - nix 0.27: POSIX signal handling

	* src/main.rs: Program entry point and global flags
	* src/error.rs: GNU ed compatible error types
	* src/buffer.rs: Line buffer data structure
	* src/carg_parser.rs: POSIX/GNU argument parser

	* README.md: Project documentation
	* CLAUDE.md: Project instructions for Claude Code
	* PRD.md: Product requirements document

	* .gitignore: Configured for Rust project
	* Justfile: Build and test automation commands
